<TITLE> Ronaldinho banned for one league match </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 LONDON, May 30 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Ronaldinho will be suspended for just one of Barcelona's remaining two league games after his dismissal against Getafe at the weekend for kicking out at defender David Belenguer. The Spanish Federation's Disciplinary Committee decided the Brazilian had been provoked after suffering a series of fouls by Belenguer. Ronaldinho will miss the game at home to city rivals Espanyol this weekend but be available for the final match of the season against relegated Gimnastic Tarragona
